---

Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are
pre-sliced!). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add steak and cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes} per side (it'll finish
cooking in Step 5). Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Once water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring,
until tender, ~{2%minutes}.

Drain, then toss noodles with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in empty pot used for noodles over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and a pinch of @salt{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until
browned and softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add scallion whites and ginger and
cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{3.5%cups}, @pork ramen stock concentrate{1}, @pho stock
concentrates{2}, and @beef stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce heat to low. Add the @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%ounce} and simmer
until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Quarter @lime{1}. Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems.

Very thinly slice steak against the grain.

Add sliced steak to broth and cook to desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn
off heat; stir in juice from half the lime. Taste and season with @salt{}.

Divide noodles and sliced steak between #large soup bowls{}; pour broth over
top.

Drizzle soup with @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon} and as much @sriracha{2%teaspoon}
as you like. Garnish with scallion greens and cilantro. Serve with remaining
lime wedges on the side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.